The paper deals with the design of linear transceivers for multi-cell wireless networks, which involves the processing of channel state information (CSI) and optimization of network-wide quality of service (QoS). This falls under the scope of information theory (cs.IT), networked systems (cs.NI), control systems (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and machine learning (cs.LG) as the paper discusses algorithms for centralized and distributed optimization.
